    {
        "taxonomy_key": ('INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY', 'Technical Support Associate', '2–5'),
        "jd_text": "ARVIND GCC\nRole Title:\tTechnical Support Associate\nFunction:\tInformation Technology - GCC IT Operations\nReports To:\tIT Support Manager\nExperience:\t3-5 years; prior experience in a GCC/shared services environment preferred\nLocation:\tAhmedabad\nRole Overview\nThe Technical Support Associate handles the day-to-day technical needs of GCC users fixing what's broken, setting up what's new, and keeping people working. This is a hands-on, ticket-by-ticket role covering Tier 1 and Tier 2 support, delivered in person at the desk and remotely. It's an execution role, not a planning one: the IT Support Manager sets direction and process; this role is where that process gets carried out, issue by issue, every day.\nWhat You'll Do\nPick up tickets, calls, and walk-ups from GCC users and resolve hardware, software, and account issues  laptops, printers, peripherals, OS, and standard business applications.\nProvide deskside support for issues that need a physical visit, and remote support for everything else, using standard remote-assistance tools.\nSet up new laptops and desktops for joiners  imaging, software installs, and standard configuration  and handle returns/recovery when people exit or move.\nHandle routine Active Directory and Microsoft 365 tasks as assigned  password resets, account unlocks, mailbox access, basic license/license-group changes.\nTroubleshoot everyday connectivity issues  Wi-Fi drops, VPN access, network printer setup  and escalate to the network team when the fix is beyond desk-level access.\nLog every ticket properly: clear notes, accurate categorization, and timely updates so users always know where their issue stands.\nRecognize when something is beyond Tier 1–2 scope and escalate it to the IT Support Manager or the right specialist team, with the diagnostic steps you've already tried.\nKeep IT asset records current  tagging new equipment, updating allocations, flagging anything missing or due for return.\nMust-Have Skills\nHands-on troubleshooting on Windows 11 hardware, OS, and common business software.\nBasic Active Directory and Microsoft 365 administration  account, password, and access tasks.\nComfortable doing both deskside visits and remote sessions in the same day.\nBasic networking know-how  Wi-Fi, VPN, network printers  enough to fix the simple stuff and describe the complex stuff clearly when escalating.\nClear, patient communication with users who don't think in technical terms.\nDisciplined ticket hygiene  nothing falls through the cracks.\nGood to Have\nExperience supporting a GCC, shared services centre, or similar multi-business-unit setup.\nBasic exposure to O365 administration\nCompTIA A+ or an equivalent foundational certification.\nFamiliarity with imaging/deployment tools such as Intune or Autopilot.\nExperience & Education\n3-5 years in a helpdesk, desktop support, or technical support role, with real Tier 1-2 ticket ownership  not just call-taking. Bachelor's degree in IT, Computer Science, or a related field, or equivalent hands-on experience.\nWhat We Offer\nA front-row seat to every part of the GCC's IT environment, working directly under the IT Support Manager, with room to grow into Tier 3 specialist or systems administration work as you build experience here.",
        "metadata": {'source_doc': 'Technical_Support_Associate_JD.docx', 'extracted_date': '2026-06-25'},
    },
    {
        "taxonomy_key": ('LEGAL & COMPLIANCE', 'Head Legal', '12+'),
        "jd_text": 'ARVIND SMARTSPACES\nDesignation: Head of the Department - Legal\nExperience: 10+ Years\nQualification: Law Graduate from a Premier Law Institute / National Law School\nDepartment: Legal\nReporting To: Chief Operating Officer\nJob Location: Ahmedabad, Gujarat\nBrief Description of the Role:\nThe Head – Legal should be able to analyse and identify the legal risks and implications of the business transactions, keeping the senior management informed of developments in laws and regulations that potentially affect the business of the Company. He should have a strong legal acumen and understanding to be able to independently head the large department. He should have Experience of working with senior legal professionals on various drafting and litigation matters.\nJob Profile:\nThe Candidate is expected to do the following on an ongoing basis:\n- Drafting of MOUs, Term Sheets, Agreements, Commercial Contracts and Agreement to Sell, Conveyance Deeds, Notices, Security Documents and other transaction and structuring of documents pertaining to Real Estate business.\n- Understand, review and comment on the Title due diligence.\n- Understand various court processes and advise the management on legal strategy.\n- Liaise with authorities like Revenue, Stamp, RERA, etc.\n- Ensure compliance of various applicable laws.\nSkills & Attributes:\n- Strong legal acumen and drafting skills.\n- Strong Communication skills.\n- Knowledge of Real Estate transactions, drafting, relevant laws and RERA.\n- Ability to read and understand Gujarati or Kannada will be an added advantage.\n- Knowledge of Gujarat and/or Karnataka Revenue Laws.\nNote: Interested candidates with relevant experience in real estate industry may share their CVs through email at career.asl@arvind.in. Please mention the position applied for in the subject of the email.',
        "metadata": {'source_doc': '2-JD-Head-Legal (2) (1).docx', 'extracted_date': '2026-06-25'},
    },
    {
        "taxonomy_key": ('MAINTENANCE & ENGINEERING', 'Administration & Facility Management', '12+'),
        "jd_text": 'Central Head Administration and Facility Management :\nKey Purpose of the Job\nShall be responsible for managing wide array of facility management functions including Operation & Maintenance, Housekeeping, Security, Cafeteria, Vendor Development, Purchase, Transport, Waste Management etc.; demonstrated capabilities in effecting business process improvements and implementing cost rationalization measures to enhance operational efficiency.\nMajor responsibilities:\nHandling operation & maintenance of the office premises.\nManaging the overall maintenance of facilities & equipments like UPS, IBMS, Access control, CCTV, kitchen equipments, Wind Solar hybrid systems, solar water heating systems, solar BIPV system, Rain water harvesting, water & sewage treatment plants, RO system, organic waste composting, fire fighting & alarm system, fire suppression system etc.\nEnsuring proper work space planning and allocation.\nManaging Help Desk & Reception, Fire & Safety, Security, Transport, Travel, VISA, Passport,  Telephone Set, EPBX system,  Cafeteria Management, Event Management, Mail Desk etc. and Housekeeping operations\nEstablishing systems & processes for improving effectiveness of the function by maintaining compliance through cost, quality & delivery\nInteracting with departments for executing maintenance of equipments/ timely delivery of new equipment and enhancing overall efficiency and customer centricity.\nInspecting field sites / facilities to observe and evaluate condition to ensure general up-keep and maintenance of premises / equipments/ appliance / furniture / furnishings / vehicles etc.\nSpearheading transport system viz., OTA/ No shows tracking/logging/checking/routing.\nFacilities to manage : Textile and garment Operations of Arvind Ltd based in Ahmedabad and Bangalore, Gujarat, Corporate Office, Envisol\nInteractions\nInternal: Business CEO and HODs , BU – HR , Finance, Accounts, IT Applications Etc.\nExternal: Vendors, Suppliers, Government bodies .\nEducational and Experience\nGraduate in any discipline\nPG Degree – any discipline\n15-20 years\nSkills and Competencies\nRelationship Management, Customer Service , Time Management, Negotiation Skills,\nInter – Personal Skills, Ability to Communicate is English and Gujarati & Team Management',
        "metadata": {'source_doc': 'Central Administration and facility mgmt.docx', 'extracted_date': '2026-06-25'},
    },
